## CLI Commands

```bash
# Sync skill repositories (wraps ru)
ms sync                     # Sync all skill repos
ms sync --parallel 4        # Parallel sync
ms sync --dry-run           # Preview changes
ms sync --status            # Status without sync

# Discover skills in synced repos
ms index --discover         # Scan ru repos for skills
ms index --from-ru          # Index only ru-managed repos

# Repo management integration
ms repo list               # List skill repos
ms repo add <repo>         # Add to ru config + skill sources
ms repo remove <repo>      # Remove from both

# Status and health
ms sync status             # Sync status summary
ms sync health             # Repo health check
```

## Exit Code Mapping

ru exit codes (from ru docs):
- 0 = All repos synced successfully
- 1 = Partial success (some repos had issues)
- 2 = Conflicts detected (need attention)
- 3 = System error (git not found, etc.)
- 4 = Bad arguments
- 5 = Interrupted (can --resume)

ms maps these for user feedback:
```rust
fn handle_sync_result(exit_code: u8) -> MsResult {
    match exit_code {
        0 => Ok(SyncSuccess),
        1 => Ok(PartialSuccess { warning: "Some repos skipped" }),
        2 => Err(ConflictsNeedAttention),
        3 => Err(SystemError("Git/ru issue")),
        4 => Err(InvalidConfig),
        5 => Ok(Interrupted { can_resume: true }),
    }
}
```

## Configuration

